### Sum of an Infinite Geometric Series

Consider the geometric series \(1+\dfrac{1}{2}+\dfrac{1}{4}+\dfrac{1}{8}+\cdots\). The common ratio is \(\dfrac{1}{2}\) and this infinite series converges.

